Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Cornell G McCarty in court with attorney Barbara K Due.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   nam

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  On motion of the State, Court ordered case dismissed with prejudice.  Bail to be returned if applicable.
Court orders a judgment for the restitution, a balance of $883.60, payable to the UW Credit Union shall revert to a CIVIL JUDGMENT and it is subject to tax intercept.

Defendant Cornell G McCarty in court with attorney Barbara K Due.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Defendant has completed TEN (10) HOURS of Community Service.  Defense advised that the Defendant gave her EIGHT HUNDRED DOLLARS ($800.00) towards restitution TODAY (02-16-2016).  Defendant advised that he has lost TWO (2) jobs due to this incident and that he is searching for employment.  State advised that they would like to see the ENTIRE amount of restitution paid in full.  State requested that Defendant keep a log of Defendant's efforts toward paying restitution and employment searches.  Based upon the defendant's compliance with Deferred Prosecution Agreement, matter is adjourned for final review hearing in Branch 33.  Review hearing scheduled for June 14, 2016 at 08:30 am.

HONORABLE JUDGE GUOLLE (RESERVED BRANCH 31) FOR HONORABLE JUDGE ACKERMAN-HAVAS (BRANCH 45) 

Defendant Cornell G McCarty in court with attorney Barbara K Due.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.

  Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum  and Elements/Jury Instructions, received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.  Court ordered case adjourned for review hearing in Branch 33.  Review hearing scheduled for February 16, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Cornell G McCarty in court.  David Robles appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Grady, Branch 23.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.   Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 9, 2015 at 08:30 am.
